◆ autosaveNeeded

void MainWindow::autosaveNeeded ( int  index = 0)
protectedslot

This function is used to trigger an autosave at the next autosave timer event. It is connected to the QUndoStack::indexChanged(int) signal so that any change to the undo stack triggers autosaves. This function can be called independent of this signal and still work properly.

References m_autosaveNeeded.

◆ backupSketch

void MainWindow::backupSketch ( )
protectedvirtualslot

A slot for saving a copy of the current sketch to a temp location. This should be called every X minutes as well as just before certain events, such as saves, part imports, file export/printing. This relies on the m_autosaveNeeded variable and the undoStack being dirty for an autosave to be attempted.

References connectStartSave(), DebugDialog::debug(), ProcessEventBlocker::isProcessing(), m_autosaveNeeded, m_backingUp, m_backupFileNameAndPath, FritzingWindow::m_fwFilename, m_sketchModel, FritzingWindow::m_undoStack, and ProcessEventBlocker::processEvents().
